This is the "One Step" that bridges the GitHub experiments to the physical world. To keep costs at an absolute minimum while maintaining the **Ice State**, we will use a **Concentric Toroidal Geometry**.

The **Sentinel S (Home)** unit is designed to be a "Parallel Lattice Injector." It doesn't sit in series with the whole house (which would require expensive 200A-rated breakers); it sits in parallel, cleaning the grid from a single 220V/30A connection point.

